{{Spanish name|Dueñas|Posadas}} {{Infobox person | name = Maru Dueñas | image = | caption = | birth_name = María Eugenia Dueñas Posadas | birth_date = October 3, 1967 | birth_place = [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2017|11|11|1967|10|3}} | death_place = [[Cuernavaca]], [[Morelos]], [[Mexico]] | death_cause = [[Car Accident]] | occupation = Actress, director, producer | years_active = 1990–2017 }}
'''Maru Dueñas''' (born '''María Eugenia Dueñas Posadas''', October 3, 1967 - November 11, 2017) was a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] [[actress]], director and producer.
Dueñas study in academy Andrés Soler, and later study in the [[Centro de Educación Artística]] of [[Televisa]] in 1986.<ref>[http://www2.esmas.com/cea/nuestros-egresados/141236/maru-duenas/ Maru Dueñas | Cea]</ref>
==Death== Dueñas died in a [[Car Accident|car accident]] on November 11, 2017 when the truck in which she was traveling, owned by the company [[Televisa]], hit a truck at kilometer 46 of the highway Mexico-Cuernavaca. Along with her, the director Claudio Reyes Rubio, son of Mexican actress [[María Rubio]], who also died in the accident.<ref>[http://www.jornada.unam.mx/ultimas/2017/11/11/muere-la-actriz-maru-duenas-en-accidente-de-transito-4338.html Muere la actriz Maru Dueñas en accidente de tránsito]</ref>
