{{for|the 18th Century French linguist and writer|Nicholas Adam}}
'''Nicolas "Nic" Dominique Adam''' (born September 18, 1881, date of death unknown) was a [[Luxembourg]]ian [[Gymnastics|gymnast]], born in [[Esch-sur-Alzette]], who competed in the [[1912 Summer Olympics]].
In 1912 he was a member of the Luxembourgian team which finished fourth in the [[Gymnastics at the 1912 Summer Olympics – Men's team|team, European system competition]] and fifth in the [[Gymnastics at the 1912 Summer Olympics – Men's team, free system|team, free system event]].
