{{more footnotes|date=March 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Sidney Franklin | image = Sidney Franklin - Jun 1920 MPN.jpg | image_size = 175px | caption = Franklin in 1920 | birth_name = Sidney Arnold Franklin | birth_date = {{birth date|1893|3|21}} | birth_place = [[San Francisco, California]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1972|5|18|1893|3|21}} | death_place = [[Santa Monica, California]] | restingplace = [[Hollywood Forever Cemetery]] | spouse = Ann Denitz (one son Sidney Jr), [[Enid Bennett]] }} '''Sidney Arnold Franklin''' (March 21, 1893 – May 18, 1972)<ref>[http://www.findagrave.com/cgi-bin/fg.cgi?page=gr&GSln=franklin&GSfn=sidney&GSbyrel=all&GSdyrel=all&GSob=n&GRid=5502&df=all& Sidney Franklin; findagrave.com]</ref> was an [[United States|American]] [[film director]] and [[Film producer|producer]]. Franklin, like [[William C. deMille]], specialized in adapting literary works or Broadway stage plays.<ref>''Silent Film Necrology'' p.181 2nd edition c.2001 by Eugene M. Vazzana</ref>
His brother [[Chester Franklin]] (1889–1954) also became a director during the [[silent film]] era best known for directing the early [[Technicolor]] film ''[[The Toll of the Sea]]''.
